oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Wood family home
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the exterior of a home belonging to James Wood. The home was built in 1832 but appears to be abandoned at the time of this photograph. There is one car parked by the house on right. Text towards the bottom of the photograph reads: "James Wood Home."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Abandoned buildings; Automobiles
